Classes/RSDFileResultUtility.html.abstract: RSDFileResultUtility is a utility for naming temporary files used to save task results.

Classes/RSDTableSection.html.name: RSDTableSection
Classes/RSDTableSection.html.abstract: Defines a section in a table. A table is made up of sections, groups and items. For most group types, there is one cell per group. The exception would be where the ui hint is for a list where each value is displayed in a selectable list.

Classes/RSDTableItemGroup.html.name: RSDTableItemGroup
Classes/RSDTableItemGroup.html.abstract: RSDTableItemGroup is a generic table item group object that can be used to display information in a tableview that does not have an associated input field.

Classes/RSDInputFieldTableItemGroup.html.name: RSDInputFieldTableItemGroup
Classes/RSDInputFieldTableItemGroup.html.abstract: RSDInputFieldTableItemGroup is used to represent a single input field.

Classes/RSDTableItem.html.name: RSDTableItem
Classes/RSDTableItem.html.abstract: RSDTableItem can be used to represent the type of the row to display.

Classes/RSDInputFieldTableItem.html.name: RSDInputFieldTableItem
Classes/RSDInputFieldTableItem.html.abstract: RSDInputFieldTableItem is a base class implementation of an input field which defaults to using a text field. Depending upon the supported UI implementations, the textFieldOptions may be ignored.

Classes/RSDChoiceTableItem.html.name: RSDChoiceTableItem
Classes/RSDChoiceTableItem.html.abstract: RSDChoiceTableItem is used to represent a single row in a table where the user picks from a list of choices.

Classes/RSDResourceConfig.html.name: RSDResourceConfig
Classes/RSDResourceConfig.html.abstract: RSDResourceConfig is designed as an overridable resource configuration manager. The functions and properties are intended to be overridable in the app by implementing a custom extension of the function with the same name. This is designed to use app-wins namespace conflict resolution that is typical of obj-c architecture.
